      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Note that the security is only comparable in your particular use case. There are other use cases (specifically, ongoing regular usage) where HD wallets are indeed less secure (because an old backup can compromise more of the current funds).\r\n\r\n(However, in those cases, you can restore a similar level of security in a more controlled manner by regularly rotating the master seed.)",
